## 3. Async Database Migration ✅

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [async_store.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/db/async_store.py) | Async VideoStore (210 lines) |
| [app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py) | Migrated `/api/library` route |

### Key Changes
- Added `aiosqlite` dependency
- Created [AsyncVideoStore](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/db/async_store.py#17-179) class with async methods
- Added [get_db_dependency()](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/db/async_store.py#208-211) for FastAPI injection
- Converted `/api/library` to use `async def` with `Depends()`

### Verification
Browser test confirmed:
- ✅ Library loads with 50 videos
- ✅ No JavaScript errors
- ✅ Service Worker registered
- ✅ 16.5 GB storage displayed correctly

